talk
Homonym Number:
Word Class: verb
Sense Number:
Definition:(of a tree) to make sounds indicating it is about to fall
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1951 R. Gilberd Okaihau That means that a tree is about to fall and the weight of the top is breaking the fibres of wood. They crackle and squeak and groan - `talking'.
Citations
Date:  0/12/1904
Source:  NZ Illustrated Magazine
Author:
Vol / Page:  178
Edition:
Quote:  `Don't you hear her talkin'?' as a gentle ticking would indicate the act of partition had commenced. Then the wedges were `backed up,' and a few solid blows from the heavy mauls would complete the operation.
